about.description: The Connectome File Format library supports handling of multi-modal neuroimaging datasets and metadata

name: cfflib
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "cfflib" %}
{% set version = "2.0.5" %}
{% set file_ext = "tar.gz" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash_value = "748043f2064079088d57a35074cf6406c436e2537e79a500330e654aadc19ac2" %}

package:
  name: '{{ name|lower }}'
  version: '{{ version }}'

source:
  fn: '{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ file_ext }}'
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ file_ext }}
  '{{ hash_type }}': '{{ hash_value }}'

build:
  number: 0
  script: python -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .
  noarch: python

requirements:
  build: 
    - python <3
    - setuptools
    - pip

  run: 
    - python <3
    - numpy
    - nibabel
    
test:
  imports:
    - cfflib
    - cfflib.tests

about:
  home: http://www.connectomics.org/
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: '{{ environ["RECIPE_DIR"] }}/LICENSE.txt'
  summary: 'Connectome File Format Library'
  description: The Connectome File Format library supports handling of multi-modal neuroimaging datasets and metadata
  doc_url: http://www.connectomics.org/
  dev_url: https://github.com/LTS5/cfflib

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - umarbrowser
